# Flutter UI / UX

## Product feel

- Cozy, collectible, shelf-oriented — premium but playful
- Imagery first; text supports visuals
- Avoid enterprise dashboards, search-engine debug copy, and cluttered layouts

## Spacing

- Use constants from `lib/core/layout/feed_rhythm.dart` (`FeedRhythm`) for tab feeds and collection shelf rhythm
- Targeted spacing tweaks over global padding inflation

## Collection / add flows

- Add-to-collection search: **series-centric** rows (one series per row)
- Subtitles: `Includes {figure}` when one figure matches; otherwise `{n} figures` and optional `• chase included` — no `Matched: A, B, C…` lists
- Tap search row → preview sheet; **Add** button → commit to shelf (do not add on row tap alone)

## Images

- Local shelf photos: `CollectibleThumbImage` + device paths; graceful placeholder on missing files
- Catalog art: `imageKey` via `CatalogImageResolver` — not on shelf models

## Code style

- Small reusable widgets; avoid massive files and excessive boilerplate
- Follow existing patterns in the feature you are editing
